That migration applies the only available strategy to mass migrate to the apphook based setup.
Any other strategy will involve a lot more work after upgrading the blog.
After applying the migrations you have to create dedicated apphooks and you can easily assign the plugins and posts accordingly to the site /appconfig they belong:

        config1 = BlogConfig.objects.get(namespace='apphook_site_1')
        config2 = BlogConfig.objects.get(namespace='apphook_site_2')
        configs = {
            1: config1,
            2: config2,
        }
        for model in (BlogCategory, GenericBlogPlugin, LatestPostsPlugin, AuthorEntriesPlugin):
            for item in model.objects.filter(app_config__isnull=True):
                if item.page:
                      item.app_config = configs[item.page.site_id]
                      item.save()

if item.page does not exists (e.g.: plugin is in a pleholderfield) you have to figure out yourself how to apply the correct apphookconfig

