@cale-sweeney In the SES Developer Guide there is an example of sending a raw email in python;

https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ses/latest/DeveloperGuide/examples-send-raw-using-sdk.html

With Amazon Simple Email Service you can send an email by passing in the subject, html body, and plain text and `send_email` will build your email message and send it with the appropriate headers. 

Raw email allows you to customize your email and requires you to pass in email header field that follow the Simple Mail Transfer Protocol. Often when composing a Raw email, users will use a library to encode the content into the correct MIME type.  For a list of MIME types that Amazon SES accepts, see [Appendix: Unsupported Attachment Types.](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ses/latest/DeveloperGuide/mime-types-appendix.html)

