@kwohlfahrt : agreed.  I will not implement the `array_output` option for now.  let me know if there is any further feedback on the conversion routine itself.  

As is, it currently can achieve perfect round trip reconstruction for any wavelets and modes for any of the multilevel transforms.  This is true for both even and odd shaped inputs.

One caveat is that it does not currently work with the single level `dwt`, `dwt2` or `dwtn` directly.  The changes to `coeffs_to_array` to support those are minimal, but adding 3 additional output_modes to `array_to_coeffs` complicates that routine substantially.  I am not sure it is worth it as one can always just set `level=1` in the multilevel transforms if only a single level of decomposition is desired.

